The paper deals with error bounds for signal reconstruction from quantized measurements, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), multimedia (cs.MM), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The use of random Gaussian projections is a common technique in compressed sensing, which falls under cs.IT and cs.SP. The paper also discusses the reconstruction of sparse signals, which is a topic in cs.LG and cs.SP. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT, cs.LG, and cs.SP, followed by cs.MM and cs.NA.
